metadata.name: Witch House
metadata.description:
Bewitched by the memory of a fantastical façade in Carmel-by-the Sea, “Witch House” channels the allegorical tides of the picturesque town. Captured at dawn amongst an audience of crows, this composition of seven hundred photos and millions of particles spin in an infinite realm. 
“Witch House” is intended to display the personification of reminiscence and how we can selectively recall memories. 

Exhibited throughout Bilbao, Spain on nine different screens located throughout the city as part of Bideotikan and Bilbao Design Week 2022.
